Function Documentation

int32_t SOC_configureDSSESMMask ( SOC_Handle  handle,
uint8_t  errorNumber,
uint8_t  mask,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This function is used to configure the bit level mask for each of the group 2 error signal connected to DSS ESM input.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the SOC Driver.
[in]errorNumberESM error number denoting the bit position that should be masked or unmasked.
[in]maskMask error flag, 0 - Unmask, 1 - Mask
[out]errCodeError code (SOC Driver Error Codes) populated on error.
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0
int32_t SOC_controlSecureFirewall ( SOC_Handle  handle,
uint32_t  firewallModulesBitmap,
uint8_t  control,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This function is used to enable/disable secure firewall for specified modules This function should be called only if the device is a secure device

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the SOC Driver
[in]firewallModulesBitmapBitmap of modules (specified by SOC_SecureFirewallModules) for which firewall needs to be modified
[in]controlSOC_SECURE_FIREWALL_DISABLE - Firewall disable (enables access to modules) SOC_SECURE_FIREWALL_ENABLE - Firewall enable (disables access to modules)
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- 0
Error- <0

double SOC_getDeviceRFFreqScaleFactor ( SOC_Handle  handle,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This function is used to get RF scale factor that can be used to translate RF frequency related (start frequency, frequency slope, frequency constant etc) configuration expressed in user-friendly units (like GHz/MHz) into units that are required for mmwavelink (and therefore MMWave) APIs related to such frequency configuration. It depends on whether the device is 60 GHz or 77 GHz device.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the SOC Driver
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
SuccessRF Frequency Scale factor
Error=0

SOC_Handle SOC_init ( SOC_Cfg *  ptrCfg,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to initialize and setup the SOC Driver. If the system clock configuration is initialized then the function will unhalt the BSS and will wait until the APLL calibiration is completed.

Parameters
[in]ptrCfgPointer to the SOC configuration
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- Pointer to the SOC Driver
Error- NULL

SOC_SysIntListenerHandle SOC_registerSysIntListener ( SOC_Handle  handle,
SOC_SysIntListenerCfg *  ptrListenerCfg,
int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
The function is used to register a listener for a system interrupts. It is possible to attach multiple listeners to a system interrupt and once the interrupt is triggered the SOC module will ensure that the registered listeners are invoked.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the SOC Module
[in]ptrListenerCfgPointer to the listener configuration
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- Handle to the System Interrupt Listener
Error- NULL

int32_t *  errCode 
)

Description
This function translates the inAddr from one domain to the other

Parameters
[in]inAddrinput address that needs to be translated
[in]directionhint on which domain to translate from and to
[out]errCodeError code populated on error
Return values
Success- valid translated address and errCode is set to 0
Error- SOC_TRANSLATEADDR_INVALID and errCode is set to SOC_EINVAL
